title: Conformal equivalence
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Two Riemannian metrics $$g$$ and $$h$$ on a manifold $$M$$ are called //conformally equivalent// if there exists a function $$u\colon M \to \R$$ such that $$g = e^{2u} h.$$ The function $$e^u$$ is called the //conformal factor.//